  {\pard\sb400\sa200\f0\fs28\b\cf2 7. Security Considerations\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  All permission checks must happen server-side. Frontend gating is cosmetic only.\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  The \f1 checkAccess\f0  helper must be called on every route that accesses transcript or folder data.\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  Cascade deletes: when a transcript/folder is deleted by the owner, all associated shares are automatically removed.\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  When a user account is deleted, all shares they created and all shares shared with them are removed.\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa200\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  Shared users must not be able to see other shared users\rquote  access. Only the owner sees the full share list.\par}

  {\pard\sb400\sa200\f0\fs28\b\cf2 8. Concurrency Note\par}
  {\pard\sb0\sa200\f0\fs22\cf1 Phase 1 uses a last-save-wins strategy. If two users with edit access save at the same time, the later save overwrites the earlier one. This is acceptable because:\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  Legal transcript editing is typically sequential (one reviewer at a time)\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  The version history system already preserves previous states\par}
  {\pard\fi-360\li720\sb0\sa200\f0\fs22\cf1 \bullet  Real-time sync adds significant complexity and is deferred to a future phase\par}

